translation.en: It's go time!
Target is half a klick southwest. Don't mess this up, seals.
translation.es: Objetivo a medio kilómetro. No metan la aleta, focas.

translation.en: I don't make mistakes.
Oh? The X47 death balloon.
This one's really deadly. Uh, I'm gonna call a human.
translation.es: Es mortal. - Llamaré a un humano. - ¡No! Nosotros podemos.

translation.en: No. We got this.
translation.es: - Llamaré a un humano. - ¡No! Nosotros podemos.

translation.en: Uh, Claggart? You-- You sure we shouldn't get a human? I- I feel like we should get a human.
translation.es: Claggart, ¿seguro? Yo digo que llamemos a un humano.

translation.en: You know, you cut the wrong wire, we'll all be boom! Agh!
- The pain! The pain! - Switch! Focus.
- Yeah, focus. Focus. - What's taking so long, Claggart?
translation.es: - Concéntrate. - Sí, globo mortal. ¿Por qué tardas tanto?

translation.en: I got a photoshoot with National Aquatic after this.
translation.es: Tengo sesión de fotos con National Aquatic.

translation.en: This isn't as easy as going Ek- ek- ek- ek- ek, Dolph!
translation.es: ¡No es tan fácil como decir ek ek, Delfino!

translation.en: Ten- hut!
Do my good boys want some tasty sardines?
We don't do this for tasty treats.
We do this for honor, for duty, for--
translation.es: Hacemos esto por honor, por deber…

translation.en: Yes, you do!
Now, give me a thumbs- up!
Run!
Claggart, I don't want to die
before... I have... my photoshoot!
translation.es: ¡Claggart! ¡No quiero morir antes de… mi sesión de fotos!

translation.en: Oh, wait, I'm a dolphin. I'm totally fine!
translation.es: Un momento. Soy un delfín. ¡Estoy bien!

translation.en: Brace for impact!
So, what's the plan?
Really obvious head- first charge.
Got anything less stupid?
How about the old 1- 2- 17, back, forward, inside- out maneuver!
translation.es: ¿Qué tal la maniobra 1-2-17, atrás, adelante, mariposa?

translation.en: Yeah, too complicated.
Ooh! Surprise attack!
- Too obvious. - Hm.
Super- secret surprise attack?
Three.
Two...
Super- secret surprise attack!
Quinn, why do you always have to shout out the name of the plan?
translation.es: Quinn, ¿por qué siempre gritas el nombre del plan?

translation.en: I got carried away. But it was such a good plan. Come on!
translation.es: Me dejé llevar. Era buen plan. ¡Vamos!

translation.en: What are you doing?
There could be you- know- what's lurking out there!
A few ravenous seal- eating sharks is nothing for the bravest seal in the ocean.
translation.es: Unos tiburones voraces comefocas no son nada para esta foca valiente.

translation.en: I, the Great Geraldo, once escaped from an aquarium
translation.es: Yo, el Gran Geraldo, escapé una vez de un acuario

translation.en: using only my wits and perfectly symmetrical features.
translation.es: usando solo mi ingenio y mis rasgos simétricos.

translation.en: Have you been waiting for someone to come past so you could tell that story?
Perhaps.
Perhaps not.
It's all part of my mystique.
translation.es: Todo es parte de mi mística.

translation.en: We can still see you.
Oh, come on. Let's go home.
We'll catch a fish tomorrow.
No. We're gonna get a fish today.
- I don't know, Quinn. - Stay here.
I'll be back before you can say, This is a really stupid idea.
translation.es: Volveré antes de que digas que es muy mala idea.

translation.en: This is a really stupid... Ugh!
Quinn! Wait up!
Come on, man. This is way better than a fish.
translation.es: Admítelo, es mejor que un pez.

translation.en: Oh, yeah?
- You don't even know what it is. - Oh, come on.
translation.es: - Ni siquiera sabes qué es. - ¡Por favor!

translation.en: Of course, I do.
It's a super- awesome, um, shiny thingy.
translation.es: Es una cosa genial y reluciente.

translation.en: - A super- awesome whaty- whaty? - Did you see that?
Do you think it would make a difference if I pretend I didn't?
Who wants to get in my face- hole?
- Out of the way! - No! Find your own lunch!
- Swim for your lives! - We're doomed!
translation.es: ¡Naden por sus vidas! - ¡Es el fin! - ¡No quiero ser comida!

translation.en: I don't wanna be food!
Hey, Snap, your face went right into...
Other way, man. Other way!
Are you crazy? There's sharks back there!
Turn around! Turn around!
Benji?
Benji!
Oh. That was too close.
Come on. We're almost home.
I said, you're going in the face- hole!
translation.es: ¡Dije que se metan en mi boca!

translation.en: No! My face- hole!
Any ideas?
Don't say super- secret surprise attack!
The corkscrew spin!
- You sure about this? - Nope, not at all.
Three... two...
Corkscrew spin!
No wonder they didn't wanna go in your face- hole.
translation.es: Con razón no querían meterse aquí.

translation.en: It's disgusting in here.
After them!
- - Quinn?
Yeah?
You shouted out the name of the plan again.
translation.es: ¡Gritaste el nombre del plan otra vez!

translation.en: But we totally nailed it that time.
Do you count not catching a fish and almost being eaten by a shark three times as nailing it?
translation.es: ¿Es genial no atrapar peces y casi ser comida para tiburones?

translation.en: Yes.
Kinda, sorta, maybe, not really, no not at all.
translation.es: Un poco, tal vez, no, para nada.

translation.en: Definitely not. That was a complete, total failure.
translation.es: Un poco, tal vez, no, para nada. Fue un fracaso total.

translation.en: - This is my spot! - No, it's mine!
Mine, mine, mine.
translation.es: - No, es mía. - ¡Mía! - ¡No me iré! - ¡Es mía!

translation.en: You do know what you did out there was really stupid, right?
translation.es: Sabes que lo que hiciste fue muy estúpido, ¿no?

translation.en: Stupidly worth it! Check it out! We could use them to make light signals!
translation.es: Pero ¡valió la pena! Mira, hace señales de luz.

translation.en: My eyes! My eyes!
I wasn't talking about the thingies. I meant coming back for me. You could've been eaten.
translation.es: No me refería a esas cosas, sino a volver por mí, fue peligroso.

translation.en: We gotta look out for each other, right?
Yeah. No matter what.
Rah! I'm a seal- eating sharky!
Tag. You're part of the food chain.
translation.es: ¡Te toqué! Eres parte de la cadena alimenticia.

translation.en: All right, little predator. It's time for dinner.
translation.es: Bueno, pequeño depredador, hora de cenar.

translation.en: Mmm. Barnacles.
- Barnacles! - Ugh!
They taste like sand and disappointment.
translation.es: Tienen sabor a arena y a decepción.

translation.en: And they're particularly disappointy- ish today.
Ugh! There has got to be a better way than this.
Oh, there is. Trick is to lick a rock for flavor.
translation.es: Sí, hay. El truco es lamer una piedra para el sabor y mirar directamente al sol.

translation.en: Then stare directly at the sun.
translation.es: El truco es lamer una piedra para el sabor y mirar directamente al sol.

translation.en: The searing pain removes the disappointment.
translation.es: El dolor intenso desplaza la decepción.

translation.en: Uh... thanks, Beth. But I was talking about all of this.
translation.es: Gracias, Beth, pero hablaba en general.

translation.en: Risking our lives every day to maybe get a fish?
translation.es: ¿Nos jugamos la vida para, con suerte, conseguir un pez?

translation.en: - I'm so sick of barnacles! - Barnacles are the worst!
Don't worry, seals. It is almost time for the sardine run.
translation.es: Tranquilas, focas. Ya casi es la migración de sardinas.

translation.en: We'll all get to eat.
- Yeah! - I love sardines!
- That totally averts any worries I had. - What about the sharks?
translation.es: - ¡Amo las sardinas! - Borra toda preocupación. - ¿Y los tiburones? - ¿Qué?

translation.en: - Sharks? - Good point.
- Oh, I did not think of that! - Ha! Hardly a concern.
I can count the amount of sharks I've seen there on one flipper.
translation.es: Puedo contar los tiburones que hay con una sola aleta.

translation.en: I'd buy that.
- Nothing to worry about. - That's pretty convincing.
- - Quinn?
Yeah?
I really hope we catch more of them awesome shiny thingies tomorrow.
translation.es: Ojalá mañana encontremos algo más que cosas relucientes.

translation.en: I'm so hungry.
What do you think these things really are?
Who knows?
All kinds of shipwrecks around here filled with weird human stuff.
translation.es: Hay todo tipo de naufragios con cosas humanas raras.

translation.en: Yeah.
My spot.
In your dreams.
He is dreaming.
Benji?
- What are you doing out here? - I'm gonna get us some food.
translation.es: ¿Qué haces? Nos buscaré comida. Hay todo tipo de naufragios.

translation.en: All kinds of shipwrecks around here, right?
translation.es: Nos buscaré comida. Hay todo tipo de naufragios.

translation.en: And humans never go anywhere without snacks.
translation.es: Y los humanos siempre llevan bocadillos.

translation.en: Now, go back to sleep.
Breakfast is on me.
Trust me, that's all I wanna do right now.
Some idiot once told me that we gotta look out for each other.
translation.es: pero un idiota me dijo que debemos cuidarnos.

translation.en: Well, that guy must have been pretty stupid.
Over here.
Humans sure have some interesting snacks.
- Junk. - Trash.
- Worthless. - Yum!
- - Sideways! Sideways! Attack!
Wow! This is a rough part of the ocean.
Tell me about it.
Oh, there's gotta be some food out there.
Yeah, like us, if we go out there.
Come on. We'll be in and out before you can say, This is a really stupid idea.
translation.es: Entramos y salimos antes de que digas que es muy mala idea.

translation.en: This is a really stupid...  I don't know why I bother.
What do you think happened...?
Why would you even think about asking a question like that? Just looking for trouble.
translation.es: ¿Cómo se te ocurre preguntar eso? ¿Quieres problemas?

translation.en: It's just that, you know, this is totally the kind of place that you would find a--
translation.es: - Parece de esos lugares donde hay… - ¡No lo digas!

translation.en: - Don't say it! - Oh, relax, man. I'm sure we'll be...
translation.es: - Parece de esos lugares donde hay… - ¡No lo digas! Relájate, todo estará…

translation.en: Sorry!
Hello there, little fellas.
- Hello. - Hello.
'Sup?
What's the rush?
I haven't even introduced myself.
My name's Grimes. How are you doing today?
translation.es: Me llamo Mugre. ¿Cómo se sienten hoy?

translation.en: - Are you good? - Are you well?
- Are you fine?  -
What? I asked if they was fine.
Like you wanted to pick the scraps off their bones.
Isn't that what we're doing here?
Obviously, but we don't want them to...
My eyes!
We can lose them in there!
- Corkscrew spin? - Are you sure?
- Hm. - Thought so.
Three.
Two. One!
See? I'm learning! I didn't even shout out the name of the plan!
translation.es: ¿Ves? Voy aprendiendo. ¡No grité el nombre del plan!

translation.en: Benji?
Come on. Come on, come on.
Come on, Benji.
Benji!
- Did he just...? - No ways.
You're food.
You're food!
No! No! Stop it!
This is so undignifying!
This is what happens when you go up against the food chain.
translation.es: Esto pasa cuando vas contra la cadena alimenticia.

translation.en: Food chain can kiss my tailfin.
translation.es: La cadena me importa un alga.

translation.en: - Hm? - No! You can't eat him! I thought you'd learned your lesson!
translation.es: ¡No puedes comértelo! ¡Pensé que habías aprendido ya!

translation.en: So, so sorry. We thought you were, oh, you know...
translation.es: Lo siento. Te creíamos… - Ya sabes. - Muerto, cambio.

translation.en: KIA, roger.
My name is Diving Dee. This is Roger.
translation.es: Yo soy Escafaldra. - Él es Cambio. - Cambio.

translation.en: - Roger. - That eloquent lady is Mayday.
translation.es: - Él es Cambio. - Cambio. Y esa elocuente dama es Auxilio.

translation.en: Is she all right?
Yeah, she's been trying to eat that starfish for years.
translation.es: Sí, hace años que intenta tragarse esa estrella de mar.

translation.en: I think they've formed a symbiotic relationship.
translation.es: Creo que tienen una relación simbiótica.

translation.en: I'm Quinn.
Well, Quinn, what brings your unconscious body to these waters?
translation.es: Quinn, ¿qué trae tu cuerpo inconsciente a estas aguas?

translation.en: I went looking for food with my friend. Benji.
translation.es: Fui a buscar comida con mi amigo. Benji.

translation.en: An old seal. He saved me from a shark.
translation.es: Y una vieja foca me salvó de un tiburón.

translation.en: Big mustache. Angry. Face like this.
translation.es: ¡De bigote grande y cara enojada como esta!

translation.en: - Ooh, Claggart. - Roger.
You know where I can find him?
You're probably safer going back to the shark.
translation.es: Estarías más a salvo con el tiburón.

translation.en: That old grouch does not like visitors. Nope.
He does seem to enjoy inflicting pain on them, though.
Oh, well, it's nice having known ya, Quinn.
Enjoy the last few moments of your short, short life.
translation.es: Disfruta los últimos momentos de tu vida.

translation.en: Over and out. Over.
You have exactly ten seconds to get off my ship
before I teach you the meaning of pain.
translation.es: o te enseñaré lo que es el dolor.

translation.en: Ten, unbelievable pain.
Nine, ridiculous pain.
Eight, worse pain.
The way you took on that shark. How did you do that?
translation.es: - Lo vi contra el tiburón. - Siete… ¿Cómo lo hizo?

translation.en: Ha! Basic flipper- to- flipper combat.
translation.es: Combate básico de aleta a aleta.

translation.en: Could you teach me?
That's what my crew used to call an RSI.
translation.es: Mi equipo catalogaría eso de MMI.

translation.en: A really stupid idea!
Why would you wanna throw your life away?
The other super awesome shiny thingy.
The whata- whata- whata- whaty?
It belonged to my best friend.
Oh. I see.
Well, it's a cold, dark, cut- the- wrong- wire - on- a- naval- mine- and- get- your- whole- team- disbanded kind of ocean out there, pup.
translation.es: El océano es frío y oscuro, y tiene explosivos que disuelven equipos.

translation.en: Weirdly specific.
It's best to go home, move on with your life, and leave complete strangers alone!
translation.es: Vete a casa, sigue con tu vida ¡y deja en paz a los extraños!

translation.en: The only way you're getting rid of me is to teach me how to fight. Or throw me off this boat.
translation.es: ¡Solo me iré si me enseña a pelear o si me tira de este barco!

translation.en: - Oh. - I-- I phrased that badly. I phrased that badly!
That lesson's for free. Now get lost.
translation.es: Esa lección fue gratis. Ahora vete.

translation.en: Teach me or the sardines are gonna get it.
translation.es: Enséñeme, o me como las sardinas.

translation.en: You wouldn't dare.
Oh. Wouldn't I?
Not the Tsardines!
Do you have any idea how difficult it is to get those?
More than anyone.
Come with me.
My years in the service taught me that this is what you need to accomplish any mission.
translation.es: Sé por experiencia que esto es lo que se necesita para cualquier misión.

translation.en: - A photo? - No! In the photo!
A dolphin smoking a cigar? No!
A team of soldiers,
translation.es: Un equipo de soldados valientes, tontos y locos

translation.en: brave, stupid, or crazy enough to follow you into any mission.
translation.es: Un equipo de soldados valientes, tontos y locos que te sigan en cualquier misión,

translation.en: No matter how dangerous.
You mean, I should form some kind of seal ensemble?
translation.es: ¿Quiere decir que debería formar como un ensamble de focas?

translation.en: - Wanna sing acapella? - Seal club?
You obviously haven't been to the Arctic. Wait. I've got it.
translation.es: - Obviamente, no sabes lo que es. - Espere. ¡Ya sé!

translation.en: Flipper Patrol!
Have fun with the sharks!
My name is Seal. You seals have been an amazing audience.
translation.es: Me llamo Seal. Fueron un gran público.

translation.en: Now, this is the part of the evening where I want you all to sing along.
translation.es: Llegó el momento en que quiero que todos canten.

translation.en: Say, Arf, arf, arf, arf, arf.
Now say, Arf, arf, arf, arf, arf. Arf. Arf!
Arf, arf, arf, arf, arf! Arf! Arf!
Now say... Quinn?
Quinn?
- Where have you been? - Where have you been?
Cut it out!
Benji and I went to...
There was a shark.
Well, it's best to forget about all that and have a barnacle.
translation.es: Bueno, mejor olvidar todo eso y comerse un molusco.

translation.en: No! I am so sick of disgusting barnacles.
Don't worry. There's always the...
What, the sardine run? Please!
We all just go into the water and hope that we're faster than the next seal.
translation.es: Todos tratamos de ser más rápidos que la foca de al lado.

translation.en: Aren't you tired of leaving your friends behind?
translation.es: ¿No les duele dejar atrás a sus amigos?

translation.en: I hate to bring up the painfully obvious, but it's a shark- eat- seal world out there, right?
translation.es: Lamento decir lo obvio, pero es un mundo lleno de tiburones.

translation.en: Every seal for themselves. If it's between him or me, I'm choosing me.
translation.es: - ¡Es la ley del océano! - Entre él y yo, me elijo a mí.

translation.en: You jerk! I thought we were friends!
- My spot! - I've been sitting here for years!
Well, I'm through running.
I'm gonna make sure we never lose another seal.
translation.es: No quiero que perdamos más focas.

translation.en: - I'm gonna fight back. -
Is there anyone here brave, stupid, or crazy enough to help me?
translation.es: ¿Hay alguna foca valiente, tonta o loca dispuesta a ayudarme?

translation.en: Actually, this isn't my spot. You can have it.
translation.es: De hecho, no es mi roca. Quédatela.

translation.en: Not even Crazy Steve is that crazy.
translation.es: Ni Steve el Loco está tan loco.

translation.en: And a shark once spat him out because he tasted too weird.
translation.es: Y un tiburón lo regurgitó porque sabía raro.

translation.en: All right, back to the music.
Please! Stop! You guys gotta listen to me.
♪ Quinn is never gonna survive ♪
♪ Because he's a little crazy ♪
Those stupid seals. Not even stupid enough to fight sharks.
translation.es: Focas tontas que no se animan a enfrentar a tiburones.

translation.en: Thanks, Beth.
But it's gonna take more than rocks and searing pain to help me.
translation.es: Pero necesito algo más que piedras y dolor intenso.

translation.en: You need seals brave, stupid, or crazy enough to fight sharks.
translation.es: Necesitas focas valientes, tontas y locas.

translation.en: You were there. How'd it go? Scale of one to ten?
Oh, Quinn. They haven't invented a number low enough to describe that.
translation.es: Quinn, no existe un número que describa lo malo que fue.

translation.en: But look on the bright side--
if you want to fight sharks, you're obviously very, very stupid.
translation.es: Si quieres pelear contra tiburones, claramente, eres un tonto.

translation.en: So you're already a third of the way to forming your own team.
translation.es: Vas encaminado para formar tu equipo.

translation.en: Yeah, you're right.
All I need is someone brave and someone...
translation.es: Solo necesito a alguien valiente y a alguien…

translation.en: Beth!
Me?
Yeah! You're always helping others! By forcing them to lick rocks.
translation.es: Siempre quieres ayudar, aunque con consejos raros,

translation.en: And you stare directly at the sun for hours, so you gotta be tough.
translation.es: y miras directamente al sol durante horas. Debes ser fuerte.

translation.en: I do have a lot of skills.
But fighting sharks is a little certain death- y for my taste.
translation.es: pero luchar contra tiburones es un poco mortal para mi gusto.

translation.en: I'll get you all the sardines you can eat.
translation.es: Te traeré un sinfín de sardinas.

translation.en: If you really wanna die a horrible death involving sharks,
translation.es: Si tanto quieres una muerte horrible con tiburones,

translation.en: I'm gonna help you achieve your goal.
Yes! Thanks! I think.
All we need now is someone brave.
Oh, easy. I know the bravest seal in the ocean.
translation.es: Fácil. Conozco a la foca más valiente del océano.

translation.en: Wow, it's a little cold tonight, hm?
Hm, it is a bit chilly.
A slightly chilly evening is nothing for the bravest seal in the ocean.
translation.es: Una noche levemente fría no es nada para la foca más valiente del océano.

translation.en: What about fighting sharks?
Fighting sharks is noth... Actually, it is quite something.
translation.es: Luchar contra tiburones no es na… De hecho, es algo.

translation.en: You brave enough to help us do it?
Me? Brave enough?
I laugh in the face of danger so much danger says to me,
translation.es: Me río tanto ante el peligro que el peligro me dice:

translation.en: Oh, Great Geraldo, you hurt my feelings.
translation.es: Gran Geraldo, no te burles de mí.

translation.en: And then I hold danger in my arms and I say,
translation.es: Y luego tomo el peligro en mis brazos y le digo:

translation.en: Sorry, I never meant to hurt you.
So is that a yes on fighting the sharks?
translation.es: ¿Eso es un sí a pelear contra tiburones?

translation.en: - Perhaps. Perhaps not. - All a part of your mystique, huh?
translation.es: Quizá sí, quizá no. Parte de tu mística, ¿no?

translation.en: You're a fast learner. I like you.
Uh, one question? How do we fight the sharks?
translation.es: Tengo una duda. ¿Cómo luchamos contra los tiburones?

translation.en: The Great Geraldo also wonders about this.
translation.es: El Gran Geraldo también se lo pregunta.

translation.en: But does not care about the answer!
I have no idea, but I know a seal who does.
translation.es: No tengo la menor idea, pero conozco a una foca que sabe.

translation.en: I found seals brave, stupid, and, uh, Beth enough
translation.es: Encontré focas valientes, tontas y a Beth

translation.en: to follow me into this mission.
translation.es: que desean unirse a la misión.

translation.en: Now will you train us?
You're persistent, pup, I'll give you that.
But only that!
This is the most blubbery, pathetic mess of a team I've ever seen!
translation.es: ¡Este es el equipo más patético que vi en mi vida!

translation.en: You don't look so hot yourself, walrus.
translation.es: Usted tampoco es un diamante, señor morsa.

translation.en: And insubordinate, too? Forget about it!
No. If you don't teach us how to fight,
translation.es: ¡No! Si no nos enseña a pelear,

translation.en: we're gonna eat every can of sardines on this entire ship.
translation.es: nos comeremos todas las latas de sardinas del barco.

translation.en: I can't promise I won't do that anyway.
translation.es: No prometo no hacerlo aunque él acepte.

translation.en: His mystique, it's... magnificent!
So, you pups think you have what it takes to be in the HMMF?
translation.es: ¿Creen tener lo necesario para estar en el HAMM?

translation.en: - Wait, your team was called hmmf? - Hmmf!
Kinda makes sense, I suppose.
It stands for Hydro- Marine Military Force,
the most elite fighting animals ever to swim in the ocean.
translation.es: ¡La mejor brigada que haya nadado en el océano!

translation.en: And I don't think you have what it takes.
translation.es: Y no creo que ustedes tengan lo necesario.

translation.en: You gotta be fighting fit, on land...
translation.es: Deben estar en forma para pelear en tierra

translation.en: and in the water.
You gotta have discipline.
- You ready to quit? - Seal, no, seal!
A lie- down would be nice, though.
You gotta be a master of stealth.
Who said that?
You gotta learn how to do a thumbs- up.
translation.es: Deben aprender a subir el pulgar.

translation.en: Yeah, we'll come back to this one.
You're gonna need...
translation.es: - Necesitarán… - Apoyo para ver al enemigo.

translation.en: - Air support to spot the enemy! - Roger that. Over.
translation.es: - Necesitarán… - Apoyo para ver al enemigo. Copiado. Cambio.

translation.en: Shoo, you stupid birds! This is my training!
Now, where were we?
You were gonna ask if we're ready to quit. And we were gonna say...
translation.es: Iba a preguntar si nos rendimos, e íbamos a decir…

translation.en: - Seal, no, seal! - Hmmf!
You're gonna learn pain.
More pain.
Pain! Pain, pain, pain, pain!
Pain! Pain.
You ready to quit?
Never!
Huh, you might just be HMMF material after all.
translation.es: Puede que sean HAMM después de todo.

translation.en: Hmmf!
That's the spirit! But you still have to pass the final test.
translation.es: ¡Así se habla! Pero aún deben pasar la prueba final.

translation.en: What test?
Fighting a shark, of course.
translation.es: Pelear contra un tiburón, por supuesto.

translation.en: Meet the fiercest predator in the ocean.
translation.es: He aquí el depredador más feroz.

translation.en: Bob.
An inanimate object is no match--
translation.es: Un objeto inanimado no es rival para…

translation.en: Is that all you've got?
Internal hemorrhaging is no mat--
